Then it is further clear, from the situation of those who consider their privilege the only God-given clue to the difficulties of life, that they must desire their leaders, if not themselves, to be held in religious honour before men, must desire the uppermost seat, the dais of the synagogue, the greeting in the market‚ the title of rabbi. As long as party-spirit prevails in saith—and the very faith of the separatist makes party- spirit inevitable———these distinctions must be coveted.
